<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <title>Recruit Members - Start a Team</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/main.css?v=13">
</head>
<body>
  <header></header>
  <main>
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/start-team" class="btn btn-secondary back-button">&larr; Back to Steps</a>
      <p class="step-label">Step 1 of 9</p>
      <h1>Recruit Members</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Click New Team to start your recruiting profile, then look for students nearby who want to build something together.</p>
      <section class="content-section">
        <p>Look for students who are curious, consistent, and willing to learn. A strong first group usually includes people nearby who enjoy building, programming, design, outreach, and organization. Starting with New Team helps you share that you are recruiting and makes it easier for nearby students to find you.</p>
        <div class="content-subsection">
          <h3>Good places to look</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Classrooms and STEM clubs</li>
            <li>Friends who like robotics, coding, or engineering</li>
            <li>Students who want to help with media, outreach, or logistics</li>
            <li>Grade levels that can stay involved over time</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <p><strong>Action:</strong> Talk to a school administrator, club leader, or nonprofit coordinator about sponsoring your team.</p>
      </section>
      <div class="step-actions">
        <a href="/start-team-step2" class="btn btn-primary">Next: Get FIRST Involved →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <script src="/assets/js/main.js?v=8"></script>
</body>
</html>
